AB  - Since most of the Korean social welfare organizations are not so large in scale, the influence of the leadership of top manager is bigger than other organizations. This study empirically tested the effects of servant leadership, which is contrary to existing vertical leadership, on the organizational effectiveness of social welfare organization members. In particular, this study tried to examine the indirect effects of organizational trust, as well as the direct effects of servant leadership on social workers’ organizational citizenship behavior and organizational commitment. Three hundred ninety-three survey data were analyzed through structural equation modeling. The results of this study showed that the direct effects of servant leadership on organizational commitment and organizational citizenship behavior as well as the mediating effects through organizational trust were statistically significant. In addition, it was found that preceding variables had a greater impact on organizational commitment than organizational citizenship behavior and that the indirect effect of organizational trust was greater than the direct effect of leadership. This study confirmed that leadership not only affects the atmosphere of social welfare organization but also affects the positive attitude of social workers. © Rushing Water Publishers Ltd. 2019.
