AB  - The public opinion ecosystem is a part of artificial social ecosystem. It composed of public opinion environment, public opinion subject and public opinion rule system. In recent years, with the advent of the era of big data, the status and influence of online public opinion has gradually become an important factor affecting the human environment. As a country that influences the interaction of various factors that promote the orderly development of public opinion, public opinion ecology plays an increasingly important role in people’s daily life quality. Whether this state is stable or not directly leads to people being able to live in peace in a community. The law of ecological balance governs the paradox of diversity and instability. Through the investigation of the current research results, it is found that the exploration of such problems has not penetrated into the more detailed analysis points of netizens. The differences and instability of the individual’s cognitive behaviors will directly or indirectly affect the changes of the entire communication mechanism. In order to study this more detailed problem, the public opinion transmission mechanism based on individual cognitive behavior in the public opinion environment is obtained through Netlogo simulation. It mainly relies on traditional infectious disease models and individual behavior patterns based on individual multi-dimensional characteristics. And choose a hot topic to get the actual law to draw and verify. The application value and significance of studying these contents lies in the fact that the dissemination mechanism and evolution law of the research can provide some reference for the relevant public opinion supervision departments and provide suggestions for them. At the same time, this study will help to form an ecological balance of public opinion and provide certain practical significance for further exploration in the future. © Foundation Environmental Protection & Research-FEPR.
